<subSubSection id="F58C4A2CECFA90449346503EDD5087E3" pageId="9" pageNumber="58" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="0E7B715233BF90A2B403E32694E7C84C" pageId="9" pageNumber="58">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1B6170068367A33430C79180B0494215" pageId="9" pageNumber="58">
Four species of 
<taxonomicName id="52BE336CFEDA56C7E1C6AFB8F4D393DA" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Triploechus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Triploechus" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Triploechus</taxonomicName>
are present in Nearctic region: 
<taxonomicName id="5F6D847CC2F56843A1B01F3EAD8DF59A" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Triploechus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Triploechus luridus" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luridus">Triploechus luridus</taxonomicName>
Hall, 1975; 
<taxonomicName id="AEB0D97A5F8BC4A18BFCEBC89E06B914" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Triploechus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Triploechus novus" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="novus">Triploechus novus</taxonomicName>
(Williston, 1893); 
<taxonomicName id="AC01AE3DE56B2AEEAB6FF5E1B4B2D8B4" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Triploechus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Triploechus sackeni" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sackeni">Triploechus sackeni</taxonomicName>
(Bigot, 1892); 
<taxonomicName id="BF8AC04CAE4D9B648DCEA7D241B3621B" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Triploechus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Triploechus stagei" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stagei">Triploechus stagei</taxonomicName>
Hall, 1975. Of these 
<taxonomicName id="2454CBCD43B7009B71CEF1DFB716C933" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Triploechus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Triploechus stagei" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stagei">Triploechus stagei</taxonomicName>
is endemic to Mexico and 
<taxonomicName id="EB2EA64E09DABFC6042B0AD0378C70DD" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Triploechus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Triploechus novus" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="novus">Triploechus novus</taxonomicName>
has the widest distribution of this genus, being present in the south of the USA and center of Mexico. 
<bibRefCitation id="BF45D45B93591D10E101B1DB788BF630" author="Hall, JC" editor="Griffiths, GCD" journalOrPublisher="E. Schweizerbart, Stuttgart" pageId="29" pageNumber="78" pagination="97 - 184" title="Bombyliidae." url="10.1163/187631283x00100" volumeTitle="Flies of the Nearctic Region" year="1981">Hall and Evenhuis (1981)</bibRefCitation>
present a revision and key for species for this genus.
</paragraph>
